main event: Multiple observers reported seeing one or two spherical objects flying in close formation over central Wisconsin.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be flying at very high speeds and were described as reddish-pink and very bright., Witnesses included reliable members of the Wisconsin County Sheriff's Department as well as many other local citizens., The sighting occurred under clear weather conditions with no unusual weather phenomena reported., Observers reported that the objects were silent and had no discernable features or exhaust trails., The observation window lasted from the night of March 24 to the early morning of March 29.
witness description: members of the Wisconsin County Sheriff's Department and other local citizens
